[1] South Sudan: outbreak
Date: Mon 28 Mar 2022
Source: Outbreak News Today [edited]
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/measles-outbreak-declared-in-south-sudan-52261/


Measles outbreak declared in South Sudan
----------------------------------------
On [23 Feb 2022], a measles outbreak was declared in South Sudan in east/central Africa. As of early March [2022], a total of 209 measles cases and 2 deaths (CFR = 0.9%) have been reported. Most cases are children under 5 years old (59.3%).

The outbreak has so far affected 3 counties of Torit, Maban and Tambura.

These 3 counties are from Eastern Equatoria, Upper Nile and Western Equatoria States, respectively.

Sporadic cases of measles have been reported in South Sudan since late 2021.

The ongoing measles outbreaks are attributed to suboptimal measles routine immunization coverage in Eastern Equatoria and Upper Nile States. Improvement in vaccination coverage is highly recommended to reduce the risk of future outbreaks. Apart from measles, rubella outbreaks have also been confirmed in Gogial West and Cueibet counties.

